column1: # In fact , the child who spends plenty of time with manipulatives ( arranging cookies on a platter , sifting flour , washing silverware ) and using real-world math ( measuring ingredients , counting celery stalks , following recipes ) has a strong foundation of representational experience , which in turn enables better understanding of abstract mathematical concepts .
